🔹 Pivot Index (1D Array)

The pivot index is an index in an array such that:

Sum of elements on the left = Sum of elements on the right

🔹 Example
Array: [1, 7, 3, 6, 5, 6]

Index:        0   1   2   3   4   5  
Left sum:     -   1   8  11  17  22  
Right sum:   27  20  17  11   6   -

At index 3 (value = 6):

Left sum = 1 + 7 + 3 = 11
Right sum = 5 + 6 = 11

✅ So, index 3 is the pivot index.


Solution:
class Solution {
    fun pivotIndex(nums: IntArray): Int {
        var prefixSum = 0
        for(i in nums){
            prefixSum += i // sum of all index
        }
        var left = 0
        for(i in nums.indices){
// main idea is to fix a index and find left sum before that index and also right sum after the index
// e.g- 0 index -> left = 0 and right = 7 + 3 + 6 + 5 + 6 = 27
            val right = prefixSum - nums[i] - left // find rightSum = total sum - current element - leftsum // right = 27
            if(left == right){
                return i
            }
            left += nums[i] // leftSum = 0 + 1 = 1
        }
        return - 1
    }

}
